{
  "work_slug": "alices-adventures-in-wonderland-by-lewis-carroll-5",
  "work_title": "Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (version 4)",
  "work_author": "Lewis Carroll",
  "audio_file": "audio-10",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/alices_adventures_1005_librivox/wonderland_10_carroll.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "10 - The Lobster Quadrille",
  "reader_name": "Eric Leach",
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.759,
  "page_num": 3,
  "page_total": 4,
  "page_start_sec": 495.58,
  "page_end_sec": 774.28,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 495.58,
      "end": 497.52,
      "text": "Her listeners were perfectly quiet till",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 497.52,
      "end": 499.28,
      "text": "she got to the part about her repeating"
    },
    {
      "start": 499.46,
      "end": 501.7,
      "text": "\"_You are old, Father William_,\" to the Caterpillar,"
    },
    {
      "start": 501.76,
      "end": 503.44,
      "text": "and the words all coming different,"
    },
    {
      "start": 503.86,
      "end": 506.08,
      "text": "and then the Mock Turtle drew a long breath, and said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 506.944,
      "end": 508.34,
      "text": "\"That's very curious.\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 509.56,
      "end": 511.4,
      "text": "\"It's all about as curious as it can be,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 511.58,
      "end": 512.28,
      "text": "said the Gryphon."
    },
    {
      "start": 513.38,
      "end": 515.0,
      "text": "\"It all came different!\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 515.42,
      "end": 517.28,
      "text": "the Mock Turtle repeated thoughtfully."
    },
    {
      "start": 517.76,
      "end": 520.56,
      "text": "\"I should like to hear her repeat something now."
    },
    {
      "start": 521.26,
      "end": 522.2,
      "text": "Tell her to begin.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 522.92,
      "end": 525.26,
      "text": "He looked at the Gryphon as if he thought"
    },
    {
      "start": 525.26,
      "end": 527.24,
      "text": "it had some kind of authority over Alice."
    },
    {
      "start": 529.152,
      "end": 530.06,
      "text": "\"Stand up and repeat",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 530.528,
      "end": 531.76,
      "text": "'_'Tis the voice of the sluggard_,'\"",
      "para_break": false
    },
    {
      "start": 531.9,
      "end": 532.82,
      "text": "said the Gryphon."
    },
    {
      "start": 533.71,
      "end": 535.6,
      "text": "\"How the creatures order one about,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 535.82,
      "end": 536.98,
      "text": "and make one repeat lessons!\""
    },
    {
      "start": 537.28,
      "end": 537.84,
      "text": "thought Alice."
    },
    {
      "start": 538.44,
      "end": 540.02,
      "text": "\"I might as well be at school at once.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 540.89,
      "end": 541.54,
      "text": "However,"
    },
    {
      "start": 541.72,
      "end": 543.54,
      "text": "she got up, and began to repeat it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 543.58,
      "end": 546.16,
      "text": "but her head was so full of the Lobster Quadrille,"
    },
    {
      "start": 546.26,
      "end": 548.26,
      "text": "that she hardly knew what she was saying,"
    },
    {
      "start": 548.4,
      "end": 550.18,
      "text": "and the words came very queer indeed:--"
    },
    {
      "start": 551.068,
      "end": 554.108,
      "text": "'Tis the voice of the Lobster; I heard him declare,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 554.388,
      "end": 557.248,
      "text": "\"You have baked me too brown, I must sugar my hair.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 557.468,
      "end": 560.308,
      "text": "As a duck with its eyelids, so he with his nose"
    },
    {
      "start": 560.588,
      "end": 563.528,
      "text": "Trims his belt and his buttons, and turns out his toes."
    },
    {
      "start": 563.828,
      "end": 566.888,
      "text": "When the sands are all dry, he is gay as a lark,"
    },
    {
      "start": 566.928,
      "end": 569.748,
      "text": "And will talk in contemptuous tones of the Shark:"
    },
    {
      "start": 570.128,
      "end": 572.848,
      "text": "But, when the tide rises and sharks are around,"
    },
    {
      "start": 573.068,
      "end": 575.58,
      "text": "His voice has a timid and tremulous sound.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 576.992,
      "end": 579.42,
      "text": "\"That's different from what _I_ used to say when I was a child,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 579.58,
      "end": 580.44,
      "text": "said the Gryphon."
    },
    {
      "start": 581.48,
      "end": 581.86,
      "text": "\"Well,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 581.96,
      "end": 583.7,
      "text": "_I_ never heard it before,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 584.02,
      "end": 584.98,
      "text": "said the Mock Turtle:"
    },
    {
      "start": 585.44,
      "end": 588.28,
      "text": "\"but it sounds uncommon nonsense.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 589.856,
      "end": 590.6,
      "text": "Alice said nothing;",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 590.78,
      "end": 592.5,
      "text": "she had sat down with her face in her"
    },
    {
      "start": 592.5,
      "end": 592.78,
      "text": "hands,"
    },
    {
      "start": 592.94,
      "end": 596.02,
      "text": "wondering if anything would _ever_ happen in a natural way again."
    },
    {
      "start": 596.98,
      "end": 598.46,
      "text": "\"I should like to have it",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 598.56,
      "end": 598.94,
      "text": "explained,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 599.44,
      "end": 600.48,
      "text": "said the Mock Turtle."
    },
    {
      "start": 601.62,
      "end": 602.78,
      "text": "\"She ca'n't explain it,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 602.86,
      "end": 603.82,
      "text": "hastily said the Gryphon."
    },
    {
      "start": 604.08,
      "end": 604.88,
      "text": "\"Go on with the next"
    },
    {
      "start": 604.9,
      "end": 605.18,
      "text": "verse.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 607.232,
      "end": 608.62,
      "text": "\"But about his toes?\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 609.12,
      "end": 610.64,
      "text": "the Mock Turtle persisted."
    },
    {
      "start": 610.98,
      "end": 613.06,
      "text": "\"How _could_ he turn them out with his"
    },
    {
      "start": 613.26,
      "end": 613.62,
      "text": "nose,"
    },
    {
      "start": 613.68,
      "end": 614.14,
      "text": "you know?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 614.8,
      "end": 616.9,
      "text": "\"It's the first position in dancing,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 617.26,
      "end": 617.94,
      "text": "Alice said;"
    },
    {
      "start": 618.38,
      "end": 619.86,
      "text": "but was dreadfully puzzled by the"
    },
    {
      "start": 619.86,
      "end": 621.8,
      "text": "whole thing, and longed to change the subject."
    },
    {
      "start": 623.24,
      "end": 624.22,
      "text": "\"Go on with the next verse,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 624.46,
      "end": 625.54,
      "text": "the Gryphon repeated:"
    },
    {
      "start": 625.78,
      "end": 626.36,
      "text": "\"it begins"
    },
    {
      "start": 626.6,
      "end": 627.7,
      "text": "'_I passed by his garden_'.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 629.152,
      "end": 630.66,
      "text": "Alice did not dare to disobey,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 630.88,
      "end": 632.32,
      "text": "though she felt sure it would"
    },
    {
      "start": 632.32,
      "end": 633.04,
      "text": "all come wrong,"
    },
    {
      "start": 633.22,
      "end": 635.0,
      "text": "and she went on in a trembling voice:"
    },
    {
      "start": 635.54,
      "end": 638.34,
      "text": "\"I passed by his garden, and marked, with"
    },
    {
      "start": 638.48,
      "end": 641.8,
      "text": "one eye, how the Owl and the Panther were sharing a pie:"
    },
    {
      "start": 642.48,
      "end": 644.84,
      "text": "The Panther took pie-crust, and gravy, and"
    },
    {
      "start": 644.84,
      "end": 645.02,
      "text": "meat,"
    },
    {
      "start": 645.18,
      "end": 648.12,
      "text": "While the Owl had the dish as its share of the treat."
    },
    {
      "start": 648.32,
      "end": 649.86,
      "text": "When the pie was all finished,"
    },
    {
      "start": 650.06,
      "end": 653.36,
      "text": "the Owl, as a boon, was kindly permitted to pocket the spoon:"
    },
    {
      "start": 653.58,
      "end": 656.02,
      "text": "While the Panther received knife and"
    },
    {
      "start": 656.08,
      "end": 657.04,
      "text": "fork with a growl,"
    },
    {
      "start": 657.04,
      "end": 658.9,
      "text": "And concluded the banquet by----\""
    },
    {
      "start": 659.06,
      "end": 662.52,
      "text": "\"What _is_ the use of repeating all that stuff,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 663.02,
      "end": 664.38,
      "text": "the Mock Turtle interrupted,"
    },
    {
      "start": 664.56,
      "end": 667.46,
      "text": "\"if you don't explain it as you go on?"
    },
    {
      "start": 668.64,
      "end": 671.98,
      "text": "It's by far the most confusing thing _I_ ever heard!\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 672.94,
      "end": 673.36,
      "text": "\"Yes,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 673.48,
      "end": 674.66,
      "text": "I think you'd better leave off,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 675.06,
      "end": 675.56,
      "text": "said the Gryphon:"
    },
    {
      "start": 675.64,
      "end": 677.8,
      "text": "and Alice was only too glad to do so."
    },
    {
      "start": 678.86,
      "end": 681.16,
      "text": "\"Shall we try another figure of the Lobster Quadrille?\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 681.28,
      "end": 682.3,
      "text": "the Gryphon went on."
    },
    {
      "start": 683.36,
      "end": 685.52,
      "text": "\"Or would you like the Mock Turtle to sing you another song?\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 686.66,
      "end": 686.94,
      "text": "\"Oh,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 686.96,
      "end": 687.5,
      "text": "a song,"
    },
    {
      "start": 687.5,
      "end": 687.82,
      "text": "please,"
    },
    {
      "start": 687.86,
      "end": 689.44,
      "text": "if the Mock Turtle would be so kind,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 690.176,
      "end": 692.28,
      "text": "Alice replied, so eagerly that the Gryphon said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 692.52,
      "end": 693.72,
      "text": "in a rather offended tone,"
    },
    {
      "start": 694.34,
      "end": 694.64,
      "text": "\"H'm!"
    },
    {
      "start": 694.64,
      "end": 695.96,
      "text": "No accounting for tastes!"
    },
    {
      "start": 696.41,
      "end": 697.68,
      "text": "Sing her '_Turtle Soup_,'"
    },
    {
      "start": 697.8,
      "end": 697.94,
      "text": "will you,"
    },
    {
      "start": 697.98,
      "end": 698.3,
      "text": "old fellow?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 698.64,
      "end": 701.1,
      "text": "The Mock Turtle sighed deeply, and began,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 701.1,
      "end": 703.4,
      "text": "in a voice choked with sobs, to sing this:--"
    },
    {
      "start": 705.28,
      "end": 708.18,
      "text": "\"Beautiful Soup, so rich and green,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 708.46,
      "end": 711.26,
      "text": "Waiting in a hot tureen!"
    },
    {
      "start": 711.84,
      "end": 714.8,
      "text": "Who for such dainties would not stoop?"
    },
    {
      "start": 714.96,
      "end": 717.84,
      "text": "Soup of the evening, beautiful Soup!"
    },
    {
      "start": 718.06,
      "end": 719.7,
      "text": "Soup of the evening,"
    },
    {
      "start": 719.92,
      "end": 721.0,
      "text": "beautiful Soup!"
    },
    {
      "start": 721.94,
      "end": 723.56,
      "text": "Beau--ootiful Soo--oop!",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 724.3,
      "end": 725.84,
      "text": "Beau--ootiful Soo--oop!"
    },
    {
      "start": 725.84,
      "end": 729.12,
      "text": "Soo--oop of the e--e--evening,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 729.46,
      "end": 732.26,
      "text": "Beautiful, beautiful Soup!"
    },
    {
      "start": 733.52,
      "end": 737.64,
      "text": "\"Beautiful Soup! Who cares for fish,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 738.06,
      "end": 741.5,
      "text": "Game, or any other dish?"
    },
    {
      "start": 742.02,
      "end": 745.56,
      "text": "Who would not give all else for two"
    },
    {
      "start": 745.82,
      "end": 749.66,
      "text": "Pennyworth only of beautiful Soup?"
    },
    {
      "start": 750.04,
      "end": 753.68,
      "text": "Pennyworth only of beautiful Soup?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 753.92,
      "end": 756.1,
      "text": "Beau--ootiful Soo--oop!"
    },
    {
      "start": 756.88,
      "end": 758.76,
      "text": "Beau--ootiful Soo--oop!"
    },
    {
      "start": 759.36,
      "end": 761.44,
      "text": "Soo--oop of the e--e--evening,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 761.62,
      "end": 764.4,
      "text": "Beautiful, beauti--FUL SOUP!\""
    },
    {
      "start": 765.9,
      "end": 766.78,
      "text": "\"Chorus again!\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 767.08,
      "end": 767.52,
      "text": "cried the Gryphon,"
    },
    {
      "start": 767.92,
      "end": 770.54,
      "text": "and the Mock Turtle had just begun to repeat it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 770.6,
      "end": 771.52,
      "text": "when a cry of"
    },
    {
      "start": 771.62,
      "end": 772.68,
      "text": "\"The trial's beginning!\""
    },
    {
      "start": 773.06,
      "end": 774.3,
      "text": "was heard in the distance."
    }
  ]
}